arChildNodes.szComment:
The Penitent Knight drops to one knee, sword in the ground before him, as if praying.
We hear the magic that drives the gears come to a grinding, painful halt and then the knight freezes in place. 
The player places their hands on the clasps of the helmet. The Knight does not move.
The player unlatches the helmet with audible, metallic “thunks”. 
As the helmet tumbles off the armor, there is an abrupt spray of blood from the neck.

As if triggered by the blood spray, the breastplate also unlocks and opens to reveal the emaciated form of Vigo, covered in blood. 
He is small in comparison to the shell he wore. Most of his body fits inside the breastplate. 
His arms extend out into the armor, pinned into place by the spikes. He appears to be crucified inside the armor.
Vigo starts, trying to sit up.
The Player pauses a moment and then nods.
Vigo nods. He speaks through pain as he struggles and then finally tears his arms free with a wet, ripping sound.
Vigo holds out the trinket to the player on a shaking, bloody hand.
Vigo looks around, seeming disoriented now, he is fading.
The player clasps their hand over the trinket, Vigo grabs on tightly.

Vigo looks over to the side where there is nothing and he smiles.
Vigo’s hand trembles and then goes limp, and his arm drops to the ground, still holding the pendant, which falls out of his hand and clinks to the ground.
